&lt;King Instrument Corp> said itreceived 8.5 mln dlrs from &lt;Otari Electric Co> of Tokyo and itsCalifornia subsidiaries as a settlement for a patentinfringement suit.    King said the suit, filed in 1980, covered a tape loadingsystem for cassettes. King said as part of the settlement,Otari must pay a royalty to King on future sales of magnetictape winding equipment in the U.S.    In a separate agreement, King said Otari has acquire fromit a non-exclusive license to King's basic patent in the U.S. Reuter&#3;